Daiwa Sees ECB Rate Cuts In December, March, Revising Its Call

-- B y   G a b i   T h e s i n g
-- 
2011-10-14T10:21:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/daiwa-sees-ecb-rate-cuts-in-december-march-revising-its-call.html
The  European Central Bank  will cut
its benchmark lending rate by 25 basis points in December and
again in March, Daiwa Capital Markets economist Tobias Blattner
said, revising a previous call that the ECB would keep its  key
rate at 1.5 percent until the end of 2012. Blattner commented in
a note to investors today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gabi Thesing at 
 gthesing@bloomberg.net  